<br>
Huh??<br>
<br>
Just cast invis on the rogue.  The same person who cast harmony can just as easily cast invis on the rogue first.<br>
<br>
Invis - does not break with spells cast on you.<br>
Hide - DOES break with spells cast on you.<br>
<br>
You can still do that tactic, just cast invis on the rogue for the same effect, without the risk.<br>
<br>
Hide breaks with any spell cast on you.  Invisibility does not.<br>
<br>
